DRG ARRIVAL TO LAND ON A LAKE AT NIGHT, THE PILOT BEGAN A 180 DEG TURN FROM 
A NE HEADING AT APPROXIMATELY 500' AGL TO A FINAL APPROACH ON A SW HEADING. AS THE AIRCRAFT 
WAS IN THE TURN, IT BEGAN LOSING ALTITUDE RAPIDLY. THE PILOT APPLIED POWER 
TO STOP THE DESCENT, BUT THE AIRCRAFT STRUCK TREES AT THE EDGE OF THE LAKE. 
THE PILOT SAID THE AIRCRAFT'S FORWARD MOTION HAD BEEN NEARLY STOPPED BY THE 
TREES BY THE TIME IT DROPPED AND CAME TO REST AT THE EDGE OF THE LAKE. 
